<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>60: Seven tens minus 1 ten would be 6 tens, which is 60.</li>
      <li>58: It’s just like the first one, but the number you’re subtracting from is 2 less, so the difference would be 2 less.</li>
      <li>58: This is like the first problem, but you’re subtracting 2 more from 70, so instead of 60, it would be 58.</li>
      <li>56: It’s like the first problem, but you’re starting with 2 less and taking 2 more, so it would be 4 less than the first answer. I subtracted tens from tens and ones from ones and ended up with 5 tens and 6 ones.</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


